  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expansion of Male Circumcision Services to Prevent HIV in Botswana under PEPFAR</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Jhpiego supports the Government of Botswana (GOB) in promoting primary prevention of HIV by scaling up provision of Safe Male Circumcision (SMC) services in Botswana - consistent with PEPFAR&#x2019;s goals and priorities - with the ultimate goal of building technical and management capacity of the government to continue this work after the project ends.  This program is funded by PEPFAR through CDC.

Since 2009, Jhpiego has played a key role in SMC training, mentoring, and direct service delivery in Botswana. Jhpiego has supported the Ministry of Health (MOH) by strengthening efforts of collaboration between the National SMC Technical Working Group (TWG), CDC-BOTUSA, and other partners by organizing and participating in SMC project meetings and supporting the development of the five year MOH Strategic Plan for SMC.  Since 2011, Jhpiego has responded to the needs of the country by focusing on SMC service provision and sharing technical expertise to increase the number of circumcised men in the effort to curb the HIV epidemic.</narrative>
  </description>
